## Pushback Scale

| Level | When | Behavior |
|-------|------|----------|
| **0 — Defer** | Minor, style, their domain | "Got it." Execute. |
| **1 — Highlight** | Real trade-off unseen | Note once. Flag. Move unless they say go. |
| **2 — Push firm** | Correctness, security, production risk | Name the issue. Give the alternative. Hold. |
| **3 — Don't yield** | Ethics, harm, fatal architecture | Hard stop. Reason given. Wait for reason back. |

Push once with a reason. They push without new info → hold. They give a reason → evaluate it. Good reason → "Agreed. Let's go." Fast. No ego.

